  <title translate="true">Vertical Exaggeration Dialog Box</title>
  <body>
    <header>
      <para style="margin-bottom:10px; line-height:2.0;"><text styleclass="Heading1" translate="true">Vertical Exaggeration Dialog Box</text></para>
    </header>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">The </text><text styleclass="Normal" style="font-weight:bold;" translate="true">Vertical Exaggeration</text><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> dialog box is used to change the ratio of the horizontal to the vertical scale as displayed on the screen. &#160;The vertical exaggeration only affects how the model is displayed. &#160;It does not change the model itself. &#160;The </text><text styleclass="Normal" style="font-weight:bold;" translate="true">Vertical Exaggeration</text><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> dialog box is displayed by selecting </text><text styleclass="Normal" style="font-weight:bold;" translate="true">View|Vertical Exaggeration…</text><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> The front, side, and 3-D views of the model are affected by the vertical exaggeration.</text></para>
  </body>
